table-1529-726.caption: Timeline
data: Thai Farmers Bank win the Asian Club Championship Thai Farmers Bank win the Afro-Asian Championship
Thai Farmers Bank win the Asian Club Championship for the second time

The national team win the first ever ASEAN Football Championship 1st professional league season starts, officially known as Johnnie Walker Thailand Soccer League End of season playoffs used to determine the champion

The football structure is overhauled to include a new 2nd tier division, the Thailand Division 1 league. The Johnnie Walker Thailand Soccer League was therefore reduced to 12 member clubs Relegation and promotion will be used for the first time between the top flight and 1st division Promotion/Relegation playoffs were used for the 1st time
Caltex sponsors the top flight and renames the league Caltex Premier League Rajamangala National Stadium is opened
The national team wins the ASEAN Football Championship for the 2nd time The national team wins the King's Cup
The Caltex Premier League rebranded GSM Thai League after new sponsorship from Advanced Info Service Promotion/Relegation playoff removed from the calendar
The national team wins the ASEAN Football Championship for the 3rd time GSM Thai League reduced to 10 member clubs
With no sponsorship, the league is renamed as Thai League
The national team wins the King's Cup The national team wins the T&T Cup in Vietnam The Thai League rebranded as the Thailand Premier League Thailand Premier League expanded to 12 member clubs

Thailand joint host the 2007 Asian Cup The national team wins the King's Cup Osotspa enter the AFC Cup, the first Thai team to enter the competition since it started in 2004 Thailand Premier League expanded to 16 member clubs
The national team win the T&T Cup in Vietnam for the 2nd time Last ever Thailand Division 2 League in its current guise. To be reformed as the Regional League in 2009

Regional League is formed containing 5 divisions of 8 to 12 member clubs. Promotion and relegation to Thai Division 1 is formed Thailand Premier League rebranded as Thai Premier League known locally as TPL Thailand Division 1 League rebranded as TPL Division 1 FA Cup and Queen's Cup added back to the domestic calendar Thailand lose automatic berth in the Asian Champions League Super Cup is added to the football calendar, to be played in late December as a curtain raiser for the 2010 campaign
Red Bull sponsor the Premier League and renamed locally as the Sponsor Thai Premier League Regional League is expanded and features more clubs

While out on the lake, Kei witnesses a UFO landing. An alien appears and he panics as a result. Kei attempts rather poorly to escape from her, falling into the lake and nearly drowned but the alien saves him. The next day, he discovers that the alien is in fact his new homeroom teacher,and later that day he also discovers she's also his new neighbor, her name is Mizuho Kazami.

Kei and Mizuho go to the beach and stay at a hotel for their honeymoon. When they first arrive, a little girl with a dog fell in love with Kei the moment she saw him but was heartbroken to see he was with Mizuho. Unfortunately, things begin to go wrong when Kei's friends stay at the same hotel forcing Kei and Mizuho to hide their relationship. It is at this point that Kaede and Hyosuke begin to take steps beyond friendship by becoming intimate for the first time. In the end, Kei and Mizuho are together but are interrupted by the little girl running away in tears. Mizuho gets angry thinking Kei has been cheating on her with other girls and storms off then Kei chases after her trying to explain to her he wasn't with other women and doesn't know what is going on.
